Talking	O
video	O
games	O
can	O
provide	O
simulated	O
voice	O
dialogs	O
between	O
human	O
players	O
and	O
animated	O
characters	O
on	O
a	O
video	O
screen	O
.	O
When	O
two	O
or	O
more	O
characters	O
are	O
in	O
two	O
different	O
scenes	O
,	O
the	O
animated	O
picture	O
may	O
alternate	O
between	O
the	O
two	O
scenes	O
to	O
give	O
an	O
illusion	O
that	O
the	O
actions	O
in	O
both	O
scenes	O
are	O
happening	O
simultaneously	O
.	O
A	O
character	O
in	O
one	O
scene	O
talks	O
with	O
a	O
character	O
in	O
the	O
other	O
scene	O
who	O
then	O
may	O
talk	O
back	O
.	O
Each	O
scene	O
branches	O
to	O
two	O
or	O
more	O
subsequent	O
scenes	O
.	O
But	O
within	O
each	O
scene	O
there	O
are	O
several	O
branching	O
dialog	O
sequences	O
,	O
thereby	O
providing	O
a	O
large	O
variety	O
of	O
possible	O
dialogs	O
.	O
Scenes	O
are	O
separated	O
in	O
space	O
or	O
in	O
time	O
.	O
The	O
characters	O
may	O
be	O
shown	O
talking	O
with	O
each	O
other	O
through	O
a	O
voice	O
communication	O
apparatus	O
such	O
as	O
a	O
telephone	O
or	O
two-way	O
radio	O
or	O
through	O
an	O
opening	O
in	O
a	O
wall	O
such	O
as	O
a	O
window	O
or	O
door	O
.	O
Each	O
player	O
has	O
a	O
hand-held	O
controller	O
that	O
displays	O
two	O
or	O
more	O
phrases	O
or	O
actions	O
.	O
A	O
player	O
responds	O
by	O
pressing	O
a	O
button	O
next	O
to	O
a	O
selected	O
phrase	O
or	O
action	O
.	O
An	O
animated	O
character	O
then	O
acts	O
or	O
verbally	O
responds	O
as	O
if	O
it	O
had	O
been	O
spoken	O
to	O
by	O
the	O
human	O
player	O
or	O
by	O
one	O
of	O
the	O
other	O
characters	O
.	O
Speech	O
recognition	O
is	O
not	O
required	O
.	O

