TECHNICAL	O
FIELD	O
OF	O
THE	O
INVENTION	O
This	O
invention	O
relates	O
to	O
video	O
games	O
,	O
animated	O
cartoons	O
,	O
and	O
human/machine	O
interaction	O
.	O

BACKGROUND	O
OF	O
THE	O
INVENTION	O
Video	O
games	O
have	O
some	O
of	O
the	O
characteristics	O
of	O
motion	O
picture	O
film	O
animation	O
.	O
In	O
film	O
terminology	O
the	O
editing	O
together	O
of	O
several	O
shots	O
in	O
a	O
sequence	O
to	O
have	O
a	O
desired	O
effect	O
is	O
called	O
montage	O
.	O
There	O
are	O
several	O
kinds	O
of	O
montage	O
.	O
Parallel	O
montage	O
is	O
alternately	O
cross-cutting	O
between	O
two	O
shots	O
or	O
scenes	O
to	O
provide	O
an	O
illusion	O
of	O
simultaneity	O
.	O
For	O
example	O
,	O
in	O
a	O
chase	O
scene	O
the	O
montage	O
alternates	O
between	O
shots	O
of	O
pursuer	O
and	O
pursued	O
.	O
This	O
illusion	O
of	O
simultaneity	O
is	O
important	O
if	O
characters	O
in	O
different	O
scenes	O
are	O
talking	O
with	O
each	O
other	O
on	O
a	O
telephone	O
,	O
two-way	O
radio	O
,	O
or	O
through	O
a	O
door	O
,	O
or	O
if	O
one	O
character	O
is	O
distantly	O
influenced	O
by	O
a	O
character	O
in	O
another	O
scene	O
,	O
either	O
by	O
hearing	O
what	O
the	O
other	O
character	O
says	O
or	O
by	O
watching	O
what	O
the	O
other	O
character	O
does	O
in	O
the	O
other	O
scene	O
.	O
For	O
example	O
,	O
a	O
character	O
in	O
one	O
scene	O
may	O
be	O
watching	O
another	O
character	O
through	O
a	O
window	O
or	O
on	O
a	O
television	O
monitor	O
or	O
the	O
like	O
and	O
thus	O
be	O
influenced	O
by	O
what	O
the	O
other	O
character	O
says	O
or	O
does	O
.	O

In	O
the	O
video	O
game	O
art	O
different	O
scenes	O
often	O
alternate	O
